page.title: 14WILDLIFE IN WOODLAND
page.content: { Birds}I have seen in{Garden and {Meadow}are:- Blue tit,great tit,long tailed tit,chaffinch,linnet,gold,green and bull finches,song and mistle thrushes,black bird,robin,swallow, house martin,field fair,yellow hammer, house,tree and hedge sparrows,sky lark meadow pipit,swift, wren, stock dove, wood pigeon,willow warbler,starling, pied wagtail,rook, jackdaw,carrion crow and magpie. { Moorland}birds are:- pheasant,snipe, partridge,sparrow hawk,kestrel, moorhen,red grouse,tawny owl,little owl,pee-wit,snipe,curlew,moorhen and red grouse.{Pond}birds are:-mallard and heron. { Sea}birds are:-herring and black headed gull. The{butterflies}are:- cabbage white, orange tip,peacock,red admiral, tortoise shell and painted lady.
